JAPAN🇯🇵 

& that’s a wrap. First international trip & boy has it opened my mind to what is out there. 
Flew into Tokyo ✈️ & stayed in Ueno📍spent a lot of time roaming the streets & eating all the street food. That’s about all we did was eat E A T eat. & lots of walking 🚶🏽‍♀️
🚆 Transportation system was easy, we only walked in circles 17374 times & hopped on the wrong bus before we got the hang of it. 
🎂 Keahi got to spend his 34th birthday eating all his favorite sushi & bottomless Kirin/High Ball.
🤼 Had a luncheon Sumo demonstration & Mālie was chosen to go against one of the sumo wrestlers 💪🏽 
🍄became “one with the world” at TeamLabs Tokyo
🚊 Took the Shinkansen down to Ōsaka📍& did a lot more eating.
🎢 Went to Universal Studio Japan & stood in ridiculous long lines, & got sunburnt but Mālie enjoyed herself & also has been dying to see Super Nintendo World for months. Never doing that again.
🏰 skipped out on Tokyo Disneyland & went to Tokyo Disney Sea instead & that was a blast. A definite must do!
We enjoyed the beauty that Japan had to offer & completely mind blown how CLEAN it is. Zero trash cans available & yet so clean. 
There’s so many in betweens that I haven’t even touched on but If you’re thinking of going to Japan, BOOK it, you won’t regret it!
Now….
Where to next?

#japantravel #mauihawaii #travelgram
